.TH BRIT 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
brit \- write stdin to stdout and a file simultaneously
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B brit
.I file
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B brit
reads from standard input and writes every byte to both standard output and
.IR file ,
similar to
.BR tee (1).
.PP
If
.I file
does not exist it is created; if it already exists it is truncated.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Wrong number of arguments.
.TP
.B 2
Cannot open
.IR file .
.TP
.B 3
I/O error during read or write.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Capture build output while viewing it:
.EX
make 2>&1 | brit build.log
.EE
.TP
Log and display a command:
.EX
./script.sh | brit script.log
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tee (1),
.BR mat (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
